+Resource models are identified from the ARM provider schema at the input level. The output library pre-creates all resources from the schema at construction time, populating a map from input model types to the resource providers generated for that model. A single TypeSpec model can be used by multiple ARM resource definitions; in that case the output library keeps one concrete `ProvisioningResourceProvider` per resource metadata entry, while ordinary references to the shared model resolve to a separate `ProvisionableConstruct` model type (model-suffixed to avoid colliding with a concrete resource class) rather than one arbitrary resource class.
 
